---
import ComponentLayout from '@/layouts/ComponentLayout.astro'
---

<ComponentLayout name='Grid'>
	<h2>Grid System Documentation</h2>
	<p>
		This utility-first grid system provides a flexible way to create responsive layouts using
		CSS Grid. It offers a 12-column foundation for precise control, along with auto-fitting and
		fixed-column options for various layout needs.
	</p>

	<h3>Core Grid Classes</h3>
	<pre><code>.grid</code></pre>
	<p>
		The fundamental class to initiate a CSS Grid container. By default, on smaller screens
		(mobile-first), it behaves as a column-stacked layout (`flex-direction: column`) and sets up
		a 12-column grid system for its children.
	</p>

	<h3>Spacing</h3>
	<pre><code>.gap-[size]</code></pre>
	<p>Applies consistent spacing (gap) between grid items.</p>

	<h3>Standard 12-Column Layout</h3>
	<p>
		The <code>.grid</code> class establishes a 12-column track. You can control the width of individual
		grid items using the following span utility classes. These classes are mobile-first, meaning
		they apply to all screen sizes by default, and can be overridden at larger breakpoints.
	</p>

	<p><code>.o-cell-full</code> Makes an item span all 12 columns.</p>

	<p><code>.o-cell-half</code> Makes an item span 6 columns (half width).</p>

	<p><code>.o-cell-one-third</code> Makes an item span 4 columns (one-third width).</p>

	<p><code>.o-cell-two-thirds</code> Makes an item span 8 columns (two-thirds width).</p>

	<p><code>.o-cell-one-fourth</code> Makes an item span 3 columns (one-fourth width).</p>

	<p>
		<code>.o-cell-three-fourths</code> Makes an item span 9 columns (three-fourths width).
	</p>

	<div class='grid'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-half'>Half</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-half'>Half</div>
	</div>
	<div class='grid'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-one-third'>One third</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-two-thirds'>Two thirds</div>
	</div>
	<div class='grid'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-one-fourth overflow-x-auto'>One fourth</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-three-fourths'>Three fourths</div>
	</div>
	<div class='grid'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs o-cell-full'>Full</div>
	</div>

	<h3>Auto Grid</h3>

	<p>
		The auto grid is useful for layouts where you want items to automatically fit and fill
		available space, wrapping to the next line as needed.
	</p>

	<p>
		<code>.grid-auto</code> Creates an auto-fitting grid. Items will automatically adjust their width
		and wrap based on the <code>--size-width</code> variable, ensuring a responsive layout without
		needing explicit column spans.
	</p>

	<div class='grid grid-auto'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>4</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>5</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>6</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>7</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>8</div>
	</div>

	<h3>Fixed Column Grids (Mobile-First)</h3>

	<p>
		For situations where you need a fixed number of columns regardless of the content, these
		classes provide direct control.
	</p>

	<h4>Single column</h4>
	<p>
		<code>.grid-cols-1</code> Forces the grid to display items in a single column.
	</p>

	<div class='grid grid-cols-1'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>4</div>
	</div>

	<h4>Two columns</h4>
	<p><code>.grid-cols-2</code> Forces the grid to display items in two columns.</p>
	<div class='grid-tablet grid-cols-2'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>4</div>
	</div>

	<h4>Three columns</h4>
	<p>
		<code>.grid-cols-3</code> Forces the grid to display items in three columns.
	</p>
	<div class='grid-tablet grid-cols-3'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>4</div>
	</div>

	<h4>Four columns</h4>
	<p><code>.grid-cols-4</code> Forces the grid to display items in four columns.</p>
	<div class='grid-tablet grid-cols-4'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>4</div>
	</div>

	<h3>Responsive Breakpoints</h3>
	<p>
		These breakpoints allow you to change grid behavior and column spans based on screen size.
	</p>

	<p><code>.grid-tablet-</code> Use grid on tablets and larger</p>
	<p><code>.grid-desktop-</code> Use grid on desktop and larger</p>
	<p><code>.o-cell-tablet-</code> Use width on tablets and larger</p>
	<p><code>.o-cell-desktop-</code> Use width on desktop and larger</p>

	<h3>Example Usage</h3>
	<p>Here are a few common scenarios and how to implement them with this grid system:</p>

	<h4>Responsive Card Layout</h4>
	<p>
		Display cards in a single column on mobile, two columns on tablet, and four columns on
		desktop.
	</p>
	<div class='grid grid-cols-1 grid-tablet-cols-2 grid-desktop-cols-4'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 1</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 2</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 3</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 4</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 5</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Card 6</div>
	</div>

	<h4>Sidebar and Main Content</h4>
	<p>A common layout where a main content area takes more space and a sidebar takes less.</p>
	<div class='grid'>
		<div class='o-cell-full o-cell-tablet-two-thirds o-cell-desktop-three-fourths'>
			<div class='card center padding-xs'>Main Content Area</div>
		</div>
		<div class='o-cell-full o-cell-tablet-one-third o-cell-desktop-one-fourth'>
			<div class='card center padding-xs'>Sidebar</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<h4>Auto-filling Components</h4>

	<p>Components that should fill available space and wrap without explicit column definitions.</p>

	<div class='grid grid-auto'>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Item A</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Item B</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Item C</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Item D</div>
		<div class='card center padding-xs'>Item E</div>
	</div>
</ComponentLayout>
